data.description: If you're in search of a historic charmer, this house may be the perfect fit for you. Located just a few blocks from the recently revitalized historic downtown Shelbyville, this home holds a special charm. Built in 1904, it boasts a range of unique features that are hard to come by. From grand tall doors and doorways to elegant pocket doors, the custom woodworking throughout adds to its allure. The generously sized rooms provide ample space, and the finished 3rd floor adds an extra touch of versatility.  The bathrooms tastefully updated in both 2019 and 2021, reflecting a modern touch while preserving the home's character. Ample storage space is a notable feature, complemented by a 2-car garage and a shed for your convenience.
